        "title": "fix(gateway): replace blocking sync I/O with async in auth/credential paths (fixes #78805)",
        "body": "## Problem\nSynchronous file I/O in auth/credential resolution paths (readFileSync, statSync, writeFileSync) could block the event loop on slow filesystems. Also blocked the auth-storage path. Fixes #78805.\n\n## Fix\nAdd async credential and config-resolution helpers. Switch auth epoch and auth-storage calls to async variants. Preserve synchronous paths for non-CLI startup.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/agents/cli-auth-epoch.ts` (+37 -10): Async auth epoch\n- `src/agents/cli-credentials.ts` (+280): New async credential helpers\n- `src/agents/sessions/auth-storage.ts` (+4 -3): Switch to async\n- `src/agents/sessions/resolve-config-value.ts` (+92): Async config resolution\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/agents/cli-auth-epoch.test.ts (passed)\n✓ src/agents/cli-credentials.test.ts (passed)\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  35 passed (35)\n```\n\n### Behavior addressed\nAuth/credential paths now use async I/O, preventing event loop blocking.\n\n### Evidence after fix\nAll 35 related agent tests pass.",
